	   <a name=966565874705></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f966565874705><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=966565874705>Using your wizard in a group</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=966565874705#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 10:31 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Far far too many wizards just don't seem to know how to play in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm goin to tell you how.  You are the final resort.  You are the one who gets the kill.  Whatever you do, don't feel you have to blast away at the Mob just because the fighters are hitting away at it.  Nothing is more annoying in a group than waiting around for a wizard who is oom because he spent way too much mana making an easy kill.  Also, nothing is more annoying than a wizard who constantly draws the Mob to him because he cast too early and runs around yelling for help.<br><br>When your tank brings in a Mob, do a /assist.  Then sit down and start medding.  Watch the tank's hit point meter and the Mob's hit point meter.  If the tank gets in trouble, by all means get up and blast away to save his butt (unless you have a healer who can do it far better then you can).  Otherwise, wait until the Mob gets to half damage, and then get up and blast away at it.  Snag those that run away an kill them.  A good wizard will almost always get the groups kill.   As soon as the battle is over, sit and med again.  You can go whole battles without more than a glimpse at what you are fighting.<br><br>Yes, you will indeed spend most of each battle sitting on your butt.  That's your job.  You're a wizard.  If you're party doesn't understand, get a better group.  They probably don't know how to play anyways.  Ideally, you should spend the same amount of time medding for mana as the tanks spend sitting for hp.  If the group is waiting around for you to gain mana, then you are casting too much.  If you are sitting around waiting for them to heal, cast more often.  Adjust your tactics for your particular group.  A properly played wizard can easily double a group's effectiveness.  A poorly played wizard is just a liabilllity.<br><br>Da Wiz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
