<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=96818574130955></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96818574130955><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96818574130955>Someone been thinking...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96818574130955#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 5th 4:29 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Very good, mostly anyway.<br><br>A wizard truly is around to save a group's ass.&nbsp;&nbsp;The potential of a wizard is very great, with full mana a wizard can take out any mob his own level or lower(assuming no resistances) all the way til the 40's.  But never have FM for long, if you are constantly FM then you are not contributing enough to the group, but dont EVER, EVER go below your evac level(assuming 1 fizzle) in a dungeon.  That backup mana is all important for the ultimate escape by evac.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
