	   <a name=9892481779656></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9892481779656><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9892481779656>RE: Using your wizard in a group</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9892481779656#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 7th 11:09 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also, if you are in a group with a warrior and a haste casting class, you can start nuking when the mob has only lost a quarter of it's life.&nbsp;&nbsp;That makes for some fast xp, and you will rarely get aggro'ed.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
