	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is an excellent area to fight in groups up to level 24, or to solo if you can get any of the single spawns to yourself. Aviak guards don't have any faction, and will never aggro on you while medding. They can be tricky to solo, though. My strategy was the old stand-by root-and-nuke. Keep Sheildskin up, or Leatherskin if you have it, and stand your ground if root breaks. By the way, if you have Enstil, don't use it. Enstil lasts longer than root, but breaks easier, so stick to root on critters you are fighting. Use Enstil to park a mob and leave alone. If you can re-root, just back off and start nuking again. For those trouble birds who just won't stay rooted, if you get below half health, cast shadow-step - it is very hard to interupt, and you can nearly always get it off. You will wind up on the bottom of the lake more than likely, where you will have all the time in the world (in most cases) to gate to safety. You might lose your spot, but it is better than dying and losing it anyway.<br>&nbsp;<br>Daeanor Endarion<br>Sorceror of the Rathe</td></tr>
