	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another thing to keep in mind is that while it is important to combat to build various skills, there are some excellent quests at lower levels that can be done repeatedly and really move the exp along.&nbsp;&nbsp;Either in CB or EC/WC, the belts quests are awesome from level 5 till like 12 or 14.  Again, after that, I agree that Oasis is ideal, or Dirv groups in N ro or WC.  The belts and lego pads in CB are espcially good, though if you are in Erude, it is quite a walk.  If you can find a TP to GFay and get a bind at orc lift (fairly easy to get the bind--takes some doing to get a TP out of Erude/Tox if you are lower level--take the boat to Queynos and shout). The one thing NOT to do as a level 1-10 wiz in Erude (IMHO) is to stay anywhere around Erude. Toxx newbie zone sucks and a little wandering there brings on elementals which will strike you dead. Quenyos and the Karana's areas are a little better, but all-in-all, I'd move to Gfay or EC/WC as soon as possible.  There are more contacts around FP, and there is always pleanty of action in and around CB.<br><br><br>Kelvyn, 30th Wiz, Veeshan <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
