	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have typically found that a small group of other similar casters works best. Especially if you can find an second Wizard and an enchanter to mez thoes mobs and give breeze once you get up there a little. Wizards take a lot of strategy and gambling in the lower levels, no doubt about it. One excellent place to camp a bit later on (like 20 or so) is the Eye Room in Beholder. Those polished Bone Bracelets sure are nice when you are 20th, and the same group above can easily hold the spawn. Add a couple of tanks and you can pull the minos at the room entrance. You can stay there getting good xp until 24th or so, at which point I recommend heading to the Lake of Ill Omen for awhile killing sarnaks and gobbos, then moving on to Dalnirs.<br>&nbsp;<br>Adesius Skyefyre<br>30th Level Wizard<br>Brell</td></tr>
