	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655919820134><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96655919820134>RE: Wizard kiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96655919820134#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43><span id=Sage>Waeloga</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>56 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 8:39 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A lower level kiting technique is the circle of death grouping with a Druid. He sows both members, then he goes out and snares (and swarms) a yellow/red beast, comes back to you (running around you in a circle), you start casting the DD's until the mob turns on you... you then run around (in a circle) as the druid casts DD's until it turns back on the druid which means you cast DD's again, etc... works from L14 druids up<br>Say L12 to L16 wizards as a start, all the way up to 24<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=96663082022355></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96663082022355><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96663082022355>Why Bother Grouping with a druid, just bring along money</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96663082022355#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=634><span id=Scholar>Altizar</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>104 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 4:33 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>No real need to group with a druid to kite, just a couple of pp will get a nearby druid to cast sow then you just tag, run and nuke.&nbsp;&nbsp;Best thing to do is not even worry about casting root, since you're going to be hunting reds anyhow, it won't work most of the time.  Just run for about 5-6 seconds then cast your spell.  You don't even have to turn around to cast it, just be sure that you have come to a complete stop before starting to cast.  Best Place for this kind of kiting is South Karana...Large areas of running room.  I soloed from 18 - 24 in this zone alone in about 2 weeks.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
